The connection between delusion and dream has occupied philosophers and physicians since ancient times.
Aristotle considered hallucinations to be a form of waking dream, Wilhelm Griesinger, one of the founders of modern psychiatry, noted in 1861 a "great similarity of the insane with dream states", for Sigmund Freud the dream was even "a psychosis, with all the inconsistencies, delusions, delusions of such".
