Kasten has been collecting reports on hallucinations and delusions for ten years, and last year he published his findings in the book "The Unreal World in Our Minds".
While hallucinations are a common symptom of psychosis, they are also a symptom of a surprisingly large number of other illnesses.
These include mental disorders such as borderline or depression, but also often include diseases such as migraines, epilepsy, multiple sclerosis or Alzheimer's and traumatic brain injuries.
Surprisingly, under certain conditions, even the brains of healthy people hallucinate.
Hallucinations, such as boxes, are composed of memory contents that are normally retained.
