Auctioning of end-of-life vehicles on the Internet
Last October, the Solera Autoonline group bought an online platform for the sale of emergency vehicles and motorcycles.
This purchase involved the payment of EUR 59.5 million for 85% of the company's capital, which could increase to the remaining 15% next year.
The purpose of this purchase was to offer its customers more services and value, with the possibility of gaining access to a huge international market.
This appraisal and purchase service is exclusively for professionals in the sector, such as insurance companies, appraisers, car rental companies, workshops, scrap yards and car dealers, who must register before their activities.
This platform was founded in Germany in 1996 and manages more than 650,000 transactions across Europe, 500,000 of which are in Germany alone.
Its main markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
The site now has over 1,500 registered sellers and 4,000 reviewers.
