The workshop's four-step cost estimate
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in just four steps:identification of the vehicle, finding the spare part, preparation and preparation of a cost estimate.
The ease of use of these systems is a fundamental requirement, especially in order to convince the older professionals, who are usually more or less against the use of these new computer technologies.
The database contains 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are motor vehicles, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with an Internet connection to use it.
After the model to be repaired has been identified by means of the chassis number, a graphic of the model appears and the required spare part is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price for hours worked, surcharges or discounts and then print out the cost estimate and pass it on to his customers.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool for evaluation like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the one targeting the workshop does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool is 350 euros a year, an amount which the customer can pay for himself.
The company Audatex is currently working on the possibility of offering these images in three-dimensional format.
This is an innovation that car mechanics have been waiting for a long time, because it allows them to select a door, for example, and then to turn the image completely around to look at the inside.
